        Summary

&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Allows to style pseudo elements that are nested inside other pseudo 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;elements. So far, support is defined for: ::before::marker 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;::after::marker With ::column::scroll-marker being supported in the 
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;future.
&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;pre style="margin: 0em;"&gt;



